@ThinkingandTinkering Very true.
I was thinking more from a conservation of energy/fuel and economy perspective.
That is also why I have been installing a rotary heat-exchanger in my house to get some of the heat out of the indoor air before it is exchanged with fresh. (Or, in summer, to get some of the heat from the outdoor air transferred back to the cooler indoor air as it gets vented.)
